%section#opscode_about_node_monitor

  #node_monitor

    .head_tool_bar

      %h1 Node Monitor

  .about

    %p
      = link_to 'Node Monitor', opscode_path
      %span is a web tool living in a Rails app at Heroku that can run and tail the chef-client on a node at Rackspace. It's able to do this through a web service the chef client provisions on the node.

    %p
      = link_to 'Node Tail', 'https://github.com/trotttrotttrott/node-tail', :target => '_blank'
      %span is the web service. It's a Sinatra app running on the node targeted by this instance of Node Monitor. It exposes endpoints to send system commands and read their output.

    %p
      %span Hosted Chef is providing the node's Chef Server. All assets are in my
      = link_to ' chef repo on Github', 'https://github.com/trotttrotttrott/chef-repo', :target => '_blank'
      %span> .

    %p
